        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Williamsport</placeName>
                <date>March 27th 1866</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p>In answer to your letter of the <date>23rd</date> inst.<lb/> I feel very much
                flattered for your kind<lb/> compliments as well in your letters<lb/> as in the late
                Occident and wish to<lb/> express you my thanks for the same. I<lb/> am very happy
                to hear you are pleased<lb/> with the progress our new Congregation<lb/> has
                hitherto made and at the same<lb/> time assure you that we get along<lb/> very
                nicely.</p>
            <p>I do not recollect if I told you already<lb/> in my last letter that my salary
                has<lb/> been increased to $ 600 a year and I<lb/> have made an agreement with
                the</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Congregation for One year that is<lb/> until <date>March 1st 1867</date>.<lb/> I am
                glad to hear you have been<lb/> taking a journey to <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                for<lb/> it assures me of your good health.<lb/> My best thanks for your kind offer
                of<lb/> assistance and whenever I shall feel<lb/> in want of your worthy advice I
                shall<lb/> take the liberty of applying to you.<lb/> Next <date>Sunday</date>
                <add>יום שני של פסח אי"ה</add> I am going<lb/> to deliver a little address to the
                Congregation<lb/> Wishing you <add>שמחת י"ט</add> and hoping you will<lb/> soon
                favour with a few lines in return</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">most respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">J S Jaiolsion <add>?</add></persName>
            </p>
            <p><persName>Miss Amelia Ulman</persName> and her parents &amp;<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Moses Ulman</persName> send their best compliments<lb/> and wish you
                happy Holidays.</p>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <ref target="Occident_PDFs/Occ_23_12.pdf">The above text refers to Occident
                        Volume 23 No. 12 page 568. Click here to view.</ref>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
